, 2018}}</ref> || 1078<ref name=SalesEurope />\n|-\n| 2011\n| 1294<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 72<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 526<ref name=SalesJapan14 /> || 889<ref name=SalesEurope />\n|-\n| 2012\n| 1188<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 117<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 558<ref name=SalesJapan14 /> || 738<ref name=SalesEurope />\n|-\n| 2013\n| 1237<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 125<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 668<ref name=SalesJapan14 /> || 480<ref name=SalesEurope />\n|-\n| 2014\n| 1436<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 125<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || n/a{{efn |name=na|Data not available}} || 503<ref name=SalesEurope />\n|-\n| 2015\n| 1105<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || 130<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || n/a{{efn |name=na}} || 486<ref name=SalesEurope />\n|-\n| 2016\n| 698<ref name=SalesGCBC/>  || 156<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || n/a{{efn |name=na}} || 618<ref name=SalesEurope />\n|-\n| 2017\n| 578<ref name=SalesGCBC/>  || 134<ref name=SalesGCBC/> || n/a{{efn |name=na}} || 816<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=https://carsalesbase.com/european-car-sales-data/nissan/nissan-gtr/|title=Nissan GT-R European sales figures|last=says|first=Naman Chawla|website=carsalesbase.com|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2018\n| 538<ref name=SalesGCBC/>  || 72<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.goodcarbadcar.net/nissan-gt-r-sales-figures/|title=Nissan GT-R Sales Figures|last=Model|website=GCBC|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref>|| n/a{{efn |name=na}} || 524<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|2019\n|331<ref name=\":1\" />\n|53<ref name=\":1\" />\n|n/a{{efn|name=na}}\n|n/a{{efn|name=na}}\n|-\n|2020\n|n/a{{efn|name=na}}\n|11<ref name=\":1\" />\n|n/a{{efn|name=na}}\n|n/a{{efn|name=na}}\n|}\n\n;Notes\n{{notelist|25em}}\n\n==Statistics by US model year==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! US Model Year\n! Power<br>kW (hp)\n! Torque<br>Nm (lb\u22c5ft)\n! {{convert|0\u201360|mph|km/h|order=flip|abbr=on|0|disp=br}}<br>(seconds)\n! {{convert|1/4|mile|m|order=flip|abbr=in|round=25|disp=br}}<br>(seconds)\n! Nurburgring Lap Time<br>(minutes)\n|-\n| 2009\n| {{convert|480|hp|kW|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| {{convert|430|ftlb|Nm|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| 3.5\n| 11.9\n| 7:26.70 <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.autoblog.com/2009/07/10/video-nissan-gt-r-files-down-ring-time-to-7-26-70/|title=VIDEO: Nissan GT-R files down 'Ring time to 7:26.70|publisher=}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2010\n| {{convert|485|hp|kW|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| {{convert|430|ftlb|Nm|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| 3.3\n| 11.8\n| NA\n|-\n| 2011\n| {{convert|530|hp|kW|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| {{convert|448|ftlb|Nm|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| 2.9\n| 11.1\n| 7.24.22 <ref name=\"AutoGuide-2011-03-24\">{{cite web|url=http://www.autoguide.com/auto-news/2011/03/2012-nissan-gt-r-724-22-nurburgring-lap-time-video.html |title=2012 Nissan GT-R 7:24.22 Nurburgring Lap Time Video |first=Colum |last=Wood |work=AutoGuide |location=Canada |date=March 24, 2011 |access-date=April 12, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2012\n| {{convert|530|hp|kW|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| {{convert|448|ftlb|Nm|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| 2.8\n| 11.0\n| NA\n|-\n| 2013\n| {{convert|545|hp|kW|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| {{convert|463|ftlb|Nm|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| 2.7\n| 10.8<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.motortrend.com/news/2013-nissan-gt-r-10-second-car/ |title=2013 Nissan GT-R is a 10 Second Car! |last=Mufthy |first=Ahamed |work=MotorTrend |location=US |date=November 7, 2011 |access-date=April 4, 2019}}</ref>\n| NA\n|-\n| 2014\n| {{convert|545|hp|kW|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| {{convert|463|ftlb|Nm|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| 2.7\n| 10.8\n| 7:19.1 <ref name=\"CarAdvice2012\">{{cite news|last=Crawford|first=Anthony|url=http://www.caradvice.com.au/199112/2013-nissan-gt-r-sets-ninth-quickest-nurburgring-lap-time-in-history/|title=2013 Nissan GT-R sets ninth-quickest Nurburgring lap time in history|date=November 5, 2012|work=CarAdvice|access-date=October 4, 2014|location=Australia}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| {{convert|545|hp|kW|order=flip|abbr=values|0}}\n| {{convert|463